inn1.comm: and he begins with a ball that could not have got closer to off stump without hitting it. Back of a length, angling in and holding its line. Brave leave from Guppy. Hmm.
130 kph, more than enough pace if you can get the ball to do magic off the seam. Lee lands it perfectly, kisses the pitch and wafts away past Guppy's nervous poke.
bat on ball finally, Lee hits the right length again, Guppy gets forward and defends carefully

he's pressing the accelerator, slowly but surely, purring up like a well-tuned engine. Short ball, hits the deck back of a length and gets lovely carry from this fresh track. Guppy weaves out of the way
hmm, 133 kph and uneven bounce. This one just hits one of those greenish clumps and dies on Guppy, goes under the bat's toe as he looks to defend
some more movement to end the over, a maiden. Lee hits the seam again and gets the away nip, past Guppy who shoulders arms. Good, intense first over
NZ are away with a wide from Tait who spears the first one well down the leg side
another one. Tait's radar is still not turned on, and Baz looks to whip another one heading down the leg. No contact made

130 kph, short delivery that came on slowly and thudded into McCullum's fore-arm. He doesn't even flinch! He's not wearing a guard, and was trying to get under the bumkper, but it did not get that high
142.3 kph, Tait hits Baz's bat and not the other way round. Short ball, fizzing up from back of a length and Baz defends into the off side

Baz is away with a typically enterprising upper-cut. Pacy from Tait again, just sligghlt wide of off stump, Baz stays beside it and uncorks those monster wrists to send it flying backward of square, almost a six
ooh, Ponting misfields, was he being careful about the injured finger? Full on the stumps from Tait, Baz leans into the push drive to the left of mid off. Ponting runs across and dives over the ball
short and into Guppy's rib cage, he rides the bounce well and fends to the leg side
Tait ends the over with another one that pings the bat hard as it jumps up from back of a length. Guppy had the forward defensive under control.
Lee angles into the stumps, Baz gets behind the line and defends to mid on
slashed away like a cheap thriller movie. Short from Lee, but not really carrying off the deck, Baz hit it hard into the ground and straight to cover
Baz turns the strike, hangs back in the crease and pushes into the covers for a single

snorta from Lee! 137 kph, lands on a length and rears up like a monster. This pitch has more ups and downs than the Himalayas. Guppy was thinking of getting forward, then saw it, wisely changed his mind, arched back and just about saved his face. Lee has some advice for him!
this one is fuller, Guppy's able to get forward and defend to the off side
another short one to end the over, steaming away at 144 kph, Guppy rises on the toes to cover the bounce and keep it down
oho, wides in the first over, now a no-ball from Taity. Baz was going after this one as it it were a free hit, huge swing and a miss to a ball wide outside off.
and the free-hit is a wide. Tait's delivered more extras than a big-budget Bollywood movie's dance would feature. Banged in real short, and it's a foot over Baz's head

finally he delivers a legal free-hit and McCullum scythes it over backward point. He almost seemed to expect another short ball, was in the position, shuffling across and throwing the willow at it. Not as well-timed as the previous hit, and it lands well short of the ropes
fuller from Tait, Baz is half forward into the defensive shot

ooh, lucky for Baz. Tait offers width again, but not as short as the other ones. Baz wanted to hit the leather off that one, but he did not have the room to crunch it away. As he was cramped, it took the inside edge and missed the stumps. French Cut for four.

McCullum has holed out, or has he? Caught at third man by Krejza, but the umpire wants to check if he over-stepped. He landed alright, but the foot skid a few inches forward. Still doesn't over-step so McCullum has to go. Full delivery outside off, Baz looks for the extravagant carve over point, but since his feet weren't across it went off the outside edge, close to the bottom of the bat. He went at that so hard, that it carried to Krejza at third man at good height.
full delivery angling across Ryder who pushes it towards cover point
width again outside off, Ryder doesn't move the feet at all and plays with an opened face, towards third man for a single
back of a length and slanting across Ryder who leaves.
135 kph, a bouncer full of intent. Ryder does the smartest thing - he ducks as it whizzes where his helmet would have been if he weren't ducking
marginally straight, back of a length at 134 kph, Ryder closes the face early as he looks to turn it away to the leg side, gets a leading edge that goes to the off side
back of a length again, not a ball to hit from Lee. Ryder is stuck on the crease, pushes his bat in front of the body to play it into the covers

145.5 kph, Lee is zipping 'em through today. Fuller and faster sucker ball outside off, it just beat Ryder for pace as he moved his feet across a year late. Close to the outside edge too. Ryder looks like a man beaten after it whizzes past

Lee is denied a maiden as Ryder threads the covers with a powerful slash into the ground. It's a shot from the Ryder book of delights, but he has it under control. A foot of width outside off, Ryder stands up and throws the bat at it, and swats it through the covers
regulation ball, angling across Guppy who stays put and shoulders arms
fuller and again angled across off, Guppy leaves again
full delivery, a yorker almost on off stump, not very pacy as Guppy digs it out between the bowler and mid off

extravagant bounce this time, got big on Guppy from back of a length and then got bigger. He tried to cut, then changes the shot into a guide, and finally into an upper cut. The ball still beat him with the extra lift
length delivery, decent pace, nothing scary - Guppy leans out and defends to the off side
Mitch tees off with a maiden, tight line and a hint of inward seam from a length on middle and off. Guppy stays in the crease and defends down the pitch
Lee beats Ryder outside off with a regulation length ball angling across and moving further away. Ryder should begin moving the feet, there is enough variation here to otherwise induce an edge
nice timing and good fielding. Similar ball from Lee, fractionally shorter, and Ryder stays back to cut it into the off side, backward point dives to the right and saves it
Ryder looks to turn off the pads, and misses. It balloons up off his body to the on side and they get a leg bye
another dot for Guppy, who stays tamely in the crease and plays defensively backward of point

Drumroll - Guptill is not out for a duck. Over-pitched on off stump and he finally gets forward with some intent, and punches through the covers. Not the best piece of timing, but good enough to get a couple. He will breathe easier

Having done his Gavaskar impersonation, Guptill now summons his inner Sehwag. Back of a length and just outside off stump. Guppy stays on leg stump, waits for the ball to come beside him, and then opens the face upwards intentionally to ping the third man boundary. Perfectly executed, almost a six. Lee ends another over with a boundary.
short of a length and angling into Ryder who steers into the covers without really getting forward
a foot outside off, but not short, Ryder looks to place him through the packed off side cordon, but point intervenes
back of a length and this time no width either. Ryder defends cautiously into the off side

don't give Ryder width, he just loves it almost as much as candy. Johndon lands this well outside off, Ryder stays rooted on his crease and swings the bat in a decisive arc to send the ball thundering through the covers.
over-compensation, very straight on leg stump, Ryder is early on the turn off the pads and plays it back down the track.
no bouncer though, length ball slanting into the pads and Ryder misses the nurdle as he continues to play, rooted to the crease
and begins with a dream away seamer. Lands back of a length outside off and just hints at going away. Guppy thought he had the line covered as he defended. He thought ...
poor line, too full and too straight, easy runs from Guppy who gets the front foot in line and whips fluidly through wide mid on
better this time, keeps it outside off and Guptill sees it through to the keeper
another one runs along the turf. 125 kph outside off, Guppy tries to play a cut on the up, but the ball just scoots below his shot.

oh well, Watto has castled Guppy with another grubber. Bad signs this, for the game. Back of a length from Watto, Guppy may have been better off coming forward in hindsight, but I doubt it would have helped. It just never came up off the track, Guppy played a half-cock forward block, but it kissed the toe of the bat and just shot through onto the stumps. Balls bounce more on nine-pin bowling alleys.
length ball to end the over, and Taylor learns from Guppy's error. Gets a good forward stride and defends to the off side

lovely pull from Ryder. Couple of things to watch in that shot. It was short from Johnson yes, but Ryder had to place it in front of square, since there was David Hussey at deep backward square leg. Secondly, he had to ensure he did not top edge it. Ryder did both, placing it in front of square, and rolling the wrists expertly over it, almost like he was playing a top-spin forehand at ping pong. Beats Hussey's dive and makes it to the fence
bonus from Mitch, Ryder likes it. Fast and sprayed down the leg side, Ryder is inside the line by design and just helps it along past short fine leg. Poor bowling at its poorest.
and it gets poorer. Wide well down the leg side.
finally Mitch hits the right length, outside off and pushes into the covers by Ryder.
back of a length and a hint wider outside off, Ryder guides it through point
very full ball at 133 kph, on off stump and pushed down the track
ends the over rather well, does Mitch. Keeps it on a tight line just outside off and Ryder opens the face to defend towards the off side
full length ball on middle and off, pushed down the track towards mid on
even fuller from Watto, this one comes in a shade, but Taylor covers the line and defends down the track again
tight from Watto, on an around off stump and on a length, Taylor defends again
short of a length and coming in to Taylor who covers the line and defends with the full face
Watto slips this in short, lots of effort for a 128 kph bumper, and Taylor gets under it
maiden from Watto, full ball hinting at inward movement, and Taylor almost falls over as he looks to work it to the leg side. Leading edge down the track. Edgy start for Taylor
again, width for Ryder, but there is a lot of protection in the off side. He tries to thump on the up through the cordon, but Clarke at cover point dives across to his left and stops it
another excellent pull from Ryder. Nice, friendly short ball from Johnson, Ryder gets inside the line and goes onto the  back foot, the front leg bent and angling in disdain, it races away square

another short one. Ryder's bowling more bouncers than you'll see in a high-end Bangalore pub. No bouncer is going to bother someone as doughty as Ryder. Again he jumps back and slaps it square. No protection in the deep. Poor bowing again from Mitch.
better length, fuller and Ryder plays it back with a straight bat.
back of a length and around off stump, the over's damage already done, Ryder just pushes it into the covers
a touch of width outside off, Ryder opens the face and steers to backward point
heavy ball from Watto, bangs it in miles short and he ducks under it. Was down the leg side too, and is called a wide
fuller and outside off, Taylor gets half forward and across to defend to the off side
slowish delivery, full at 123 kph, Taylor's struggling to get it off the square here. Guided to backward point.
fuller length and angling into the stumps, Taylor defends with the full face towards mid on

poor delivery, lets Taylor off - this is the 12th four of the innings in 13 overs; Four and dot seems to be the theme. Short and going down the leg side, Taylor got into a tangle, not knowing what to do with it, and ended up gloving it to fine leg
length ball on off stump, tamely pushed into the covers. Ian Chappell wonders why they aren't manouvering more singles
and Watto finishes the over with another friendly gift, angling down the leg side and Taylor gets some pad on it as it hurries across to fine leg.
good length around off stump, Ryder stays in his crease and drives towards cover point. Can we have some singles please?

caught behind! New Zealand are making no progress here. Johnson hits a good length around off stump and gets the ball to straighten just enough off the pitch. Ryder pushes forward tentatively and gets a thick nick through to Haddin. It's what eventually happens when you let one bowler bowl at a batsman for long periods without making him change his line by rotating strike.
and the first ball is full on middle and leg, Franklin flicks to the man placed at short square leg
shorter ball around off stump. Franklin drops his wrists, sways a little and lets the ball go past
there you go, too high at No. 5. Franklin keeps his feet rooted in his crease and tries to drive at one extremely far away from his body. Rubbish shot, and the edge is taken oh so easily by Haddin.
short of a length and very straight. Styris defends off his back foot towards the off side.

how lucky is Taylor! Tait pinged him with a rapid short ball and Taylor took his eyes of the ball, left it all to fate, and half ducked. The ball crashed into his hand, a little higher than the glove and lobbed over first slip.
wide outside off stump, left alone
fuller and straighter, Styris aims to flick but doesn't make proper contact

horrific shot from Styris and the implosion continues. Tait pitched one short and wide, Styris went to slash it but it was a bit too far from him. He needed to get a bit closer to the ball but he didn't and the edge is once again taken by Haddin.
and How gets a juicy full ball on leg stump first up, and flicks it down to fine leg. Tait was looking for the yorker
Taylor gets behind the line of a short of a length delivery and defends
short of a length ball angling across the right-hander from over the wicket, left alone by the batsman
wider ball outside off, the batsman strides forward and shoulders arms again
given the spate of edges to Haddin of late, Johnson is asking How to come and get it from wide outside off. How shows admirable restraint and says no thank you
short of a length and straighter, How jumps back and works the ball through square leg
Now the temptation is thrown at Taylor, short of a length outside off stump. Taylor also resists. If only their team-mates had shown similar discipline.
And Taylor's discipline wavers but his thick edge flies low and down to third man
Tait delivers a full ball on leg stump, Taylor leans across and flicks towards fine leg
full and straight, defended on the front foot towards the off. Tait's over-stepped so New Zealand have a chance to go crazy against the next ball
what do I know. It's a yorker but the line is down leg and it's glanced towards fine leg
very full and very straight. Taylor plays the ball rather late and drives towards mid-on
full length outside off stump, driven firmly but to the man at cover point
short of a length outside off stump, How drops his wrists and lets it go
bowled him! Tait fires a full and fast yorker at Taylor, who had no hope once he made the decision to play across the line. He played around the ball and it crashed into off stump.
left alone outside off stump
punched firmly off the front foot towards extra cover
good length around off stump, How stays in his crease and blocks
defended on the back foot once again, Johnson is bowling a testing line around off
fuller length on a tight line, pushed into the covers on the front foot
perfect line, perfect length. Johnson's third maiden. How lets it go outside off stump
full ball from Tait around off stump, driven off the front foot towards cover. New Zealand are stuck in some terrible mire here. There is a woeful lack of direction to this innings.
flicked off the front foot towards midwicket
short ball outside off stump, McCullum lets it go through to Haddin
Tait appeals but there was bat on this one. Only a little bat though and that's what saved McCullum. He too tried to play across the line to a full and fast delivery that was very straight
How flicks another full one through square leg
nudged on the leg side for one more
tossed up wide outside off stump. McCullum strides forward and towards the ball to drive to cover
driven with power through cover point, through the infield for a single
closer line from Krejza and How dabs it towards point and takes a single
nudged off the pads through square leg this time
fuller length on off and middle, How drives down the ground towards long off
whipped on to the leg side from outside off stump
McCullum attempts to cover drive but gets beaten outside off
defended on the front foot towards cover ...

Lee was aiming for the yorker but his line was a little awry on leg stump, McCullum missed the flick and the ball hit the pad and rolled towards the on-side. Lee couldn't sprint across quickly enough to prevent the run. A bit of reverse from Lee
good length outside off stump and rather quick. How lets it go safely
another full ball with a hint of swing into the right-hander, flicked off the pads behind square
good length outside off, edged towards third man for a single
tossed up outside off stump, the batsman reaches for it and plays the square drive through point
shouts of catch it as McCullum chips the ball in the air but just wide of Krejza as the bowler dived to his right to try and take the caught and bowled
flicked through the leg side for one
McCullum whips the ball through square
nudged off the pads down leg side, another single
driven towards long-on to end the over

Lee is a champion. He first delivered a good length ball at considerable pace around off stump. The batsman blocked it and then set off for a single. Lee sprinted to get the ball and slid as he did so, his feet breaking the stumps at the batsman's end. Nervelessly he turned around and on the slide scored a direct hit at the bowler's end. The batsman was in though.
full ball outside off, run down to third man
pushed towards cover on the front foot
good length once again and very straight, played towards square leg with a closed face
good length outside off stump, dabbed off the back foot towards point
an a welcome sight, McCullum keeps his eyes on the short ball from Lee and bunts it over the head of Haddin. First boundary in 11 overs.
defended on the back foot towards the off side
a full ball driven firmly towards the bowler, Krejza gets some hand on it and it narrowly misses the stumps at the bowler's end. Would have been close had it hit
defended on the front foot
McCullum moves a touch across and chips the ball high in the air towards deep midwicket where the ball falls wide of the fielder. New Zealand reach 100, it's been a tough journey there
played on the off side, towards point
an attempted cut off the back foot but the batsman tried to hit it a bit too hard and mis-timed the shot towards cover
Lee sneaks a good length ball in between the batsman's bat and pad. That one seamed in a touch and kept very low
good length and straight, How can't do much but defend
played towards square leg from the crease
Lee bowls wider outside off stump and How lets it go through to Haddin
full ball outside off stump, How leans into it and plays a crisp square drive. Injured finger and all, Ponting makes a fine save at point
another full and fast delivery outside off, How drives once again and this time Ponting makes an easier stop
the ball beats the bat and thuds into Haddin before rolling towards short third man
defended on the front foot towards the off
worked off the pads towards square leg
defended on the back foot
driven towards long on
swept on one knee towards short fine leg
that might have spun, had it pitched. McCullum takes it on the full and drives down the ground
this one pitches but doesn't turn so much. Driven back to the bowler
a loose drive to one that lands outside off. The outside edge is in the air but falls short of White at point
defended towards the bowler on the leg side
played off the back foot through square
a large stride forward precedes a solid forward defensive shot
defended on the front foot on the leg side
a flatter offering and it is cut off the back foot towards short third man
Krejza slips one down leg side, McCullum gets inside the line and tries to glance the ball. He misses but the ball beats Haddin as well
pushed through cover point for a single
edged this time for four to third man. How pushed forward at one outside off and got a thick edge that ran past the fielder at short third man
worked off the pads towards square leg
How tries to cut the ball but it's a bit quicker and beats the outside edge
tossed up on off and Nathan leans out to defend to the off side
skids across on off stump, Nathan gets half forward and opens the face to dab it square for a single
fuller on off stump, How drives strongly but straight to the fielder in the covers
this time he gets the gap between cover and mid off. Singles galore.
Nathan whips him off the pads wide of mid-on to turn the strike over again

How reviews an lbw call that looked plumb at the outset. Tossed up on middle from a touch wide of the crease, grips and straightens as How looks to defend it in front of front pad. The bat came across from its backlift, that began with the bat pointing at gully, a little late. The ball thudded into the pad in front of middle and was headed towards the stumps too. A review wasted, How is gone.
back of a length and holding its line around off stump, Nathan works it off the back foot through midwicket for a single
flighted on off, Dan leans forward and defends carefully as he smothers the spin
and turn, from leg stump, almost squares up Vettori and gets a leading edge. Thankfully, it was too thick to carry to slip. Pops up into the covers for one
Nathan shuffles across and nurdles off the pads through square leg for a single
tossed up on leg, Vettori reaches out to the line and turns the wrists for a single in front of square
sharp bounce from Krejza from middle and leg, gets big on Nathan as he tries to glance, and balloons up off the thigh to the leg side. Haddin collects and they let out a stifled appeal in hope.
Smith offers Vettori generous width outside off, and he hangs back and across to steer backward of point for one
Nathan reaches out and drives into the covers for another single. Uppish, but he was in control all the time
flatter, Vettori plays back and taps it off the pads to the leg side
tossed up on off stump, Vettori leans out and defends to the off side
turning into the pads, Vettori nurdles to the leg side. Can't get a single
Vettori jumps a mile outside the crease, converts it into a low full toss and drives, but can't beat mid off
full length ball outside off, Nathan backs away and looks to carve through the off side, but misses
over-pitched on off stump, Nathan shuffles across and looks for the off drive, but can't get it past Tait on his follow through
short of a length this time and very close to off stump, Nathan hangs back in the crease and looks to dab it with an open face towards backward point

finally Nathan gets it away for four. Not. Brett Lee is all over the place with his athleticism today. Short of a length on off stump, and Nathan under-edges a steer that runs very fine towards third man. Lee comes across, dives and prevents the boundary
short ball again, Nathan invokes his inner Brendon and looks for the heaved upper cut. He's not quite quick enough with the hands, and misses, though.
this one is speared into the pads. A touch of reverse, may be? Nathan plays all around it, and it runs away off the pads into the off side for a leg bye
tossed up generously and turning away, Nathan opens the wrists and cuts square for one
tossed up again, wide of off stump and Vettori steers it through point for one
tossed up again on off and turning away, Natha reaches out to cover the spin, and defends
Nathan goes back in the crease and whips against the spin through midwicket for one
turning into the pads this time, Vettori works him with soft hands towards midwicket for one more
over-pitched on leg stump, Nathan punches down the ground for one
Tait has landed a few horror wides today. Another one, a mile outside off stump. Wide as the mid-section of a Sumo champion.
better this time, angles in at sharp pace from just outside off. Nathan is doing a good job of connecting with thin air. Pity that's not getting him any runs.
smart footwork, Nathan gets the front foot across to off stump and works it off the pads as it angles in, and picks a couple to backward square leg.
145 kph, too fast for this McCullum, who again throws his bat at it outside off and misses
swish, swoosh, miss, miss. This time Nathan plays the perfect on-the-up cover drive. And misses, as Tait whizzes by as good pace
sharp bouncer, coming in with the angle from wide of the crease and heading for the head. Nathan wisely ducks
a foot outside off to end the over, for a change Nathan leaves
outside off, Vettori is on the front foot and pushes into the covers
Vettori gets the single with quick wrists, worked off the pads through midwicket
Nathan bunts a full delivery past the bowler down the ground for one
wide outside off, Vettori can't reach it and it is called
closer to off stump this time, and Vettori manages to dab it with an opened face towards third man
flighted on leg stump, Nathan drives with the spin to the left of mid off and turns the strike over again
Vettori retains strike, reaching out to a full-pitched delivery and driving to the left of mid on for one more

Australia have reviewed an lbw appeal that was turned down. Interesting one this - it is a full toss that lands flush on the foot, in front of leg stump. Remember, the ball hasn't landed and spun, which it might well have done if it hand landed. Umpire Doctrove reckoned it would have carried on with its trajectory, and headed down the leg side. The decision stays.
full delivery again, this time it lands. Vettori leans out ad defends
pad and bat? Or the other way? Polite appeal from Krejza as he fires in the armer around off stump, and Vettori plays from the crease.
and he does Vettori in the air as he skips out, Krejza shortens the length and forces Vettori to rethink his shot. Poked out to the off side

poor delivery, and Nathan pounces on it with hungry intent. Short delivery, sat up and asked to be hit to the leg side, Nathan seemed unable to control his glee as he rocked back and cracked it through midwicket
back of a length and turning in, worked with the spin to midwicket for one
Nathan plays with the spin into the covers
back of a length on the pads, worked off the pads to the leg side, but straight to the fielder
waits for the spin and defends to the leg side. Aus are finally zipping through the overs
over-pitched on middle and leg, Nathan plays it back down the track powerfully, but straight to the fielder
Nathan finally gets the single, steering with the spin, with an angled face through point
Vettori taps Smith off the pads to midwicket and ends with another single
straightens from Vettori's pads, he works it off the backfoot in front of midwicket for one
tossed up on middle and leg, whipped without power to midwicket
shortens the length, but is still on middle and leg from round the wicket. Nathan waits and glances off the hips through square leg
very straight and tight, on middle and leg, blocked off the back foot down the track
Vettori sweeps from well outside off, and does well to keep it down. Single to deep midwicket
short of a length on middle and off, Nathan motors across to off stump and turns him through square leg for another single
tossed up on off, Nathan drives nicely with the spin but finds cover
Nathan loves a short ball, and Australia's spinners are giving him enough to stay happy. Shocker from Smith, Nathan is ready on the back foot and carts it through midwicket. Emphatically dealt with.
tossed up and worked with the spin into the off side

nicely done by Nathan, stays put on leg stump and waits for the ball to come beside him before cracking it on the up ythrough the covers. The ball does more damage on the way, to Ponting's finger as he dives to his left in an attempt to stop it. He's in pain now.
speared on middle and leg, Nathan punches strongly down to long on for one

too cheeky from Nathan for his own good. Tossed up well outside off, he tries to work it from there to the leg side, without getting the foot across. The kind of shot only Moin Khan can pull off. Nathan misses and it misses the stumps too.
fifty to Nathan, calmly gets forward and taps towards cover point for a single.
tossed up outside leg and turning in, Vettori looks to paddle sweep and finds short fine leg

It's the Trans-Tasman sweepstakes, and Vettori is striking it rich. Tossed up outside off, but he'd picked his spot early. Gets done low, crouches in anticipation and then creams it through midwicket. Along the ground, and into the gap.
and a different version of the sweep now, the paddle dab as Krejza lands outside leg. A single to short fine leg
Nathan taps it from leg stump towards mid on. Can't get the single though
this time Vettori tries the reverse sweep and misses.
tossed up on off stump, Vettori reaches out and drives efficiently down the grounf
extra turn from Smith, gets the outside edge but Nathan plays it softly so it doesn't carry anywhere. Single towards cover. Fifty runs added.
Vettori stays back and plays to the off side for a single
Nathan forces a short of length ball from off stump towards deep cover for another single
on Vettori's pads and sliding further down, he glances it fine and gets a single
angles into the pads first up, at 139.2 kph, but no worries for Vettori as he gets the pads inside the line and helps it along to fine leg

Nathan reviews an lbw decision. Another interesting one, as Mitch landed on middleand leg. The ball was doing nothing, just carried on with the line. Nathan, for some reason, was looking to get across to the off stump and nurdle to the leg side. A fine plan that, but not if you miss the plan. He did. Hit in the front of middle, and it was carrying on to hit off. Both reviews done for New Zealand, and an important wicket for Aus.
yorker on off stump, dug out down the track. Southee is the new man in by the way.
edged but White is standing too deep at lone slip to hold it. Pitched up and asking to be driven, Southee goes for it and gets a thick edge. Straight to White, on the bounce
very straight, on middle and leg as Southee hops away and works it to the leg side.
Vettori chips across to off stump an tucks him square for one. Will he take the batting Powerplay now?
tossed up outside off, Vettori drives expansively to deep cover for two
tossed up on off, skidding along, and Vettori tries to play another reverse slap. Misses this time
and Vettori makes contact with the reverse sweep now. Such a good looking shot when it comes off. Smith tosses it up outside off, Vettori reverses the grip and sends it packing through third man
horror delivery, full toss on leg and took everyone by surprise. Vettori was so shocked, he fell down as he made contact with a powerful pull-sweep. Made good contact though, and picked up four more.
plays down the ground for a single. Good batting from the captain here.
Southee looks to cut a short ball, but finds point. Vettori has strike
back of a length and very straight, Vettori begins with anti-climactic defence down the track
just outside off this time, Vettori stays on the crease and chops it behind square for a single.
he misses the first ball, back of a length and angling across as he looks to poke to the off side from the crease
a stolen legbye to change strike. Mitch lands this on the pads, following Southee as he hops away, and they squeeze a single towards backward point

Vettori is playing a really good innings here. Again. Jumps away to leg stump to open up the off side, and Mitch tries to cramp him by landing it on middle and leg, but Vettori had enough room to force an off drive and get it to the right of mid off

there's more shuffling here than happens before the dealing of a Poker hand. Vettori skips across to off stump, Mitch has no idea where he is going and lands this outside leg stump. It's a wide, and Vettori feels he missed out on the flick
again, Vettori trots across to well outside off, Mitch follows him correctly and Vettori can't do much except work it to the leg side for one
slow bouncer, 121 kph and Vettori says Thank You very much! That sat up like a dolly and Vettori slapped it happily through midwicket
more improvisation. Vettori again hustles across to off stump and gets one on the pads. He clips it away with ominous timing towards deep backward square leg, and Tait does well to cover it
more runs, Southee gets a thick edge that nearly runs away for four towards third man, but Tait again does well
Southee jumps away, Lee follows him like a guided missile and Southee ends up completely cramped, jumping away in clumsy fashion as it squeezed in towards him

they are hurting Australia here. Southee, in the manner of all defiant tail-enders, is just staying rooted to the crease and waving at them outside off. This one is back of a length and he gets it to deep cover for three.

after seven brilliant wicket-less overs, Lee picks one  in his shoddiest over of the day. Vettori has run more at the crease today than between them, and again motors away to well outside off. Lee does well to stick to his guns and keep it outside off, back of a length. Vettori goes for the pull and gets an inside edge, through to Haddin.

Ponting is saved a hefty fine for slow over rates as Australia manage to bowl New Zealand out, just five minutes over time. Poor, poor shot from Southee. Looks to launch a straight length ball without getting forward, and just tonks it up in the air. It goes up into the Nagpur sky and when it comes down, Ponting is ready, despite the fact that the midday sun would have blinded him.

inn2.comm: short ball to begin with, but the line is down leg side and that's a wide
good length outside off stump, Watson comes forward to drive with power but mis-times the ball towards the bowler
Watson waits on the ball and opens the face to dab down to third man
another wayward ball down leg side, poor control from Southee
good length outside off stump again, considerable pace and bounce to the wicketkeeper after the batsman shoulders arms
a hint of shape away from the right-hander from a good length, Haddin pushes towards mid-off to get going
fuller ball on middle, Watson comes forward and flicks towards midwicket
terrific footwork, Haddin jumps forward and towards leg to create room and drills the ball through extra cover with a powerful drive. It was a length delivery and Haddin simply hit through the line
defended on the front foot towards the off
Watson strides forward and blocks with bat and pad close together
Watson pushes the ball off the front foot from middle stump towards wide mid-on for one
Haddin flicks the ball from a full length on middle towards midwicket
pushed off the front foot towards point
Watson moves deep into the crease and forces the ball towards wide mid-on off the back foot
Southee strays on to the pads again and Watson plays the good length ball towards midwicket

that didn't quite go where Haddin wanted it to but he's got the same result. He was aiming to go through midwicket with the flick but got a very thick inside edge through square leg, good timing on the shot
played on the off side from the crease
Haddin steps down and makes room once again to drive inside out through extra cover, this time he doesn't time it as well or find the gap
the slower ball pushed off the back foot towards mid-on for one
good length ball angling into the right-hander, Watson stays in his crease and defends on the leg side
Haddin stays in his crease and plays a square drive towards deep point
defended on the leg side from deep in the crease
a bit of room from Vettori and Watson plays a powerful square cut off the back foot towards deep point where Franklin can't prevent the second
the sweep this time and a single to deep square leg
superb shot, Haddin didn't try to hit it too hard. He just looked to make contact and place it over the head of the fielder at mid-off, the timing's good enough to take the ball to the boundary
played on the leg side off the front foot
Haddin tries to make room to hit Southee through the off again but ends up having to play it back to the bowler
short and wide, Haddin begins to create room and then realises he doesn't need to. He simply swats the ball through cover with perfect timing and placement
strays on to the pads this time and there's an easy single on offer after pushing the ball towards midwicket
Watson nudges the ball towards square leg for a risky double, Haddin was struggling at the non-striker's end had there been a direct hit

Southee pitched the ball outside off and seamed it into Watson, who tried to flick but missed. The ball struck the pad and Southee's appeal was upheld by the umpire. Watson asked for a review right away and replays show the ball going down leg side and over the stumps
Watson gets tucked up by a short of a length delivery that rises a touch sharply into the mid-section. Watson wanted to work the ball through square but ended up defending it
the first ball is full and on leg stump, Haddin picks it off his pads with a flick towards deep midwicket
Bennett cramps Haddin for room with one that pitches around off and jags into the right-hander. Haddin fends the ball towards short fine leg
McCullum dives superbly to his left to prevent the wide down leg side from running to the boundary
short of a length and straight. Haddin stays on the back foot and defends
defended from the crease once again towards the on side
full ball and down leg side, ripe for flicking, but Haddin can't make contact and gets hit on the pad
Haddin jumps back and across and flicks the ball firmly off his pads towards short fine leg
Watson gets on to the front foot and drives a length delivery with power towards mid-off
Haddin hints at making room again, but then stays rather motionless, and chops a short of a length ball towards third man
fuller ball angling into the right-hander. Watson moves forward and drives towards mid-on
a loud appeal from Southee but the umpire, Kumar Dharmasena, says not out this time. Watson got hit in front while defending but there was a big inside edge
defended on the back foot towards the bowler
Watson stays in his crease and opens the face to guide a good length delivery angling towards him to the fielder at point
Bennett pins Haddin to the crease with pace from a good length. Haddin gets behind the line on off stump and blocks
strays on to leg this time and Haddin clips it off his pads towards deep midwicket. Williamson has to run around from deep square to field. Williamson is on the field for Styris.
poor ball, too full and too far down leg side. McCullum's dive can't prevent the five wides this time
full ball outside off stump, Watson tries to drive and mis-times it towards point
a slower ball but it's also a lovely full toss on leg stump at knee height. Watson waits and swats it to the long leg boundary

Watson punches the ball firmly down the ground and beats the fielder diving across from mid-on. Nathan McCullum tears after the ball from mid-off and dives full length, arms flailing in front of him, and pulls the ball back in just before the boundary
poor line and length, full on leg stump. Haddin glances it off his pads past a diving McCullum
full ball swinging into the pads and Watson flicks with power towards deep midwicket where Franklin does the fielding
Haddin makes room for a short of a length delivery and carves it in the air and over point, there's no one in the deep so Australia pick up steam with another boundary
good length delivery outside off, Haddin stands his ground this time and drives to cover
fuller length on middle stump. Haddin opens up his stance and lofts the ball cleanly over wide mid-on for four more
slightly slower from Southee and Haddin swings and misses. The ball thuds into McCullum's pads and goes towards short fine leg
Haddin swings again and gets a bottom edge towards short fine leg
flat delivery on middle stump, defended on the back foot
cut off the back foot towards deep point
played late off the back foot and the batsman places the drive in front of point
sublime shot, all timing and placement. Haddin made a bit of room and simply eased the drive through the gap between cover and mid-off. Vettori gave chase but the ball kept gaining ground
played on the off side from the crease
played back to the bowler
good length and rather straight. Played back to the bowler.
driven off the front foot towards the bowler again.
driven from the crease towards cover. McCullum is standing up to the stumps
defended with a straight bat towards the bowler
played back to the bowler once again
Ryder's ruined a good over with a shocking ball down leg side. With McCullum standing up, he has no chance.
Watson hammers the drive towards long-on
punched on the back foot towards the bowler
width offered outside off and Watson cuts hard off the back foot towards cover. Vettori scored a direct hit but Watson was home
forced off the back foot towards cover point
pushed back towards the bowler once again
Watson drives off the front foot towards mid-off where Vettori fumbles. Guptill backs up from extra cover
played towards midwicket
played towards short fine leg for a single
pushed off the front foot towards point
full ball on middle and leg, Haddin drives towards long on to reach his half-century
full ball down leg side. McCullum collects as Watson misses the flick and whips off the bails in a flash. Watson had overbalanced but managed to keep his back foot grounded
length ball on of stump and Watson sends it screaming own the ground with a powerful drive towards long-on
nudged towards midwicket front the crease
a slow delivery from Ryder, Haddin plays it towards cover
width offered outside off stump and Watson moves on to the back foot and plays the square cut with power to the deep point boundary
driven off the front foot towards cover, McCullum is bowling rather quick
muscled towards deep midwicket this time. Hit hard and flat and it reaches the fielder on the bounce
Haddin taps the ball gently towards mid-off and sprints the single
short ball and Watson heaves the ball off the back foot. He spotted the length early and absolutely hammered it over the deep midwicket boundary
played towards midwicket
poor line, down leg side and Watson glances the ball towards fine leg
extremely wide outside off stump
driven though cover point off the front foot
a touch short and Watson pulls the ball towards deep midwicket
the bouncer and the batsman lets it go
Watson strides forward and plays the cut towards point
played towards deep midwicket for a single to end the over
Watson lunges forward and plays a powerful slow seep towards deep midwicket. It's flat but in the air so the fielder at deep midwicket tries desperately to catch it, in vain.
Watson swats this, bludgeons this with unbelievable power to the wide long-on boundary. He hit that on one knee and extremely hard and flat
a slower ball from Vettori and Watson hits the ball hard through the off side this time
cut hard off the back foot towards deep point
Haddin moves back and blocks
short delivery, bowled with no intent, Watto picks the slower ball and smashes a pull to deep midwicket
another short one, but this time had pace behind it. Haddin pulls but can't time the shot
back of the hand slower delivery, 104.9 kph and well executed. Haddin was no where near picking that, and played all over it as it hit the pads, outside the line of off
another bouncer, 138 kph and steep lift, Haddin gets over it and rolls the wrists over it for a single to deep square leg

such a poor short ball, even the lack of bounce on it did not prevent Watto from pulling for four. It did not bounce at all, and he seemed in some trouble as he adjusted the shot with the ball headed for his midriff. Still puts it away for four
and now one well outside off, Watto can't reach it.
another wide delivery, close to being called too, as Watto has a biff and misses
tossed up on the pads, Haddin politely pushes it towards long on and picks one
big spin for Vettori, but so late in the day. Lands back of a length outside off and spits away past Watto's backfoot prod. Outside edge goes towards the slips.. which are vacant.
tossed up on leg stump again, Haddin again works it against the spin for a single to mid on

Bad to worse to shambles for NZ. Williamson drops a catch in the deep as Watto looks to mow a short ball, and plays it straight at Williamson who was slow moving forward and tumbling ahead. Should have been taken
Haddin chips him off the pads through midwicket for one more
Vettori ends the over with a dot ball as Watto can't get it away

Bennett gets Haddin with a 96.4 kph slow bouncer. Comical stuff all round. It came out much shorter than Bennett wanted - landed midway down the pitch, took off in slow motion and seemed to stop - in mid-air mind you - as Haddin evaluated his options. He decided to throw the horizontal bat at it and swat it down, but it was too high for him to control. He ended up looping it to deep midwicket, despite rolling the wrists over it, and this time Franklin holds.
this one angles into Watto's pads and he tucks it square for a couple
very wide outside off and Watto can't reach it though he wants to

Bennett has picked two in two. Do NZ have a chance to get back into this? Once again, Watto perishes soon after crossing his 50. Bennett continues to operate with that nagging lack of pace, this time back of a length and well outside off. Watto waited for it to come on and played an ugly cross-batted swipe. The ball was coming slower than he expected, and took the inside edge before crashing into the stumps.
slips onto Pup's pads and he's eases behind square for one
short ball, nipping into Ponting from wide of off stump as he hops into line. Fended off bat and pad towards fine leg. Ponting was not very comfortable dealing with that

Bennett's over has ended before 2011 came to an end. Eventful over, finished with another one of those back of the hand deliveries, this one was very full and sliding down the leg. Worked along to fine lef for a single
tossed up on the pads, Clarke works it wide of mid on and turns the strike
tailing in towards leg stump and straightening, Ponting covers the line and taps it square on the leg side
tossed up on middle and off, Clarke comes forward to smother and defend
holds the length back and lands this a foot outside off, Clarke reaches across and defends to the off side
Clarke skips out, gets close to the pitch but chooses to play it back down the ground
fuller on leg and middle, Clarke is compact in his forward defensive
bangs it in back of a length outside off, Ponting rides the bounce and defends to the off side
again the slow legcutter at 104.9 kph, but sliding too far down the leg side. Ponting gets inside the line and helps it along to fine leg for a couple
another short delivery, Clarke gets behind the line and controls the pull to keep it down in front of square leg for one
Is he over-doing these now? Another back of the hand slower ball that slips down the leg side and is called wide
angled into the pads again, worked easily off the backfoot for a single,

Bennett is pre-programmed to bowl just two types of balls in this spell - the bouncer and the slow legcutter. Clarke seemed to know what was coming, jumping inside the line and camping on the backfoot as this bouncer slanted in. Easy runs for him, latched on early and pulled emphatically in front of square
ends the over with a variation. Back of a length outside of, Clarke hops back and defends
tossed up on Ponting's pads, he reaches out and defends

easy runs. Third man inside the circle, and Vettori lands this short and well outside off. Ponting jumps on it with the cut shot and gets a thick outside edge that beats the fielder and runs to the boundary at third man
turning away from middle and off, Ponting gets back and defends to the off side
tossed up this time, Ponting reaches out and defends to the off side
again, back of a length and Ponting stays on the crease to defend into the off side
Ponting defends the last ball, gets behind the line and defends down the track
back of a length on the stumps, he opens the face and dabs it backward of point for one

huge appeal for caught behind, and it is being reviewed. Slants down the leg side as Ponting tries to play the glance off the front foot. Did he get a feather on it? Replays are not conclusive - we need HotSpot and Snicko for this. McCullum was convinced the way he went up - very very confident. Well, the umpire's decision has been upheld. NZ lose a review.

another huge appeal, this time for lbw. Will they review this? No. This one is fuller, comes in off the seam from well outside off, prodigious movement for Southee as Ponting pushes forward and outside the line. Replays say that wwas hitting him just in line. And it was headed to middle stump. They should have reviewed this one!
back of a length again, this one is a legcutter and goes away subtly. Defended into the off side by Ponting.
and the pressure is released with a poor ball slanting into the pads, Ponting clips it along the way for a couple to fine leg
definite reverse for Southee, another one jars in sharply as Ponting thinks of getting the front foot forward and across, he ends up playing around it but gets it down to long on for one
back of a length and turning across, he pushes forward and defends into the off side
similar delivery, Clarke reaches across and defends into the off side
this one straightens from middle and off, Clarke hangs back and forces against the deviation into the off side for one
this one is a grubber that slips down the leg side, Called a wide
Ponting gets a single this time, staying back and punching into the covers for one
Clarke gets well forward and defends down the track
another dot ball, back of a length on middle and leg and Clarke defends down the track
another legcutter from Southee, Ponting spots it off the track, covers the line and defends down the track
short of a length and angling in from just outside off, at 139 kph, and Ponting pushes it into the off side off the back foot
fuller this time and tailing in, Ponting works it off the pads, but can't beat the two men standing at midwicket
Full and straight, Ponting arrests the forward movement and brings the bat down in time to play it towards mid on
angles this one across Ponting who stays on the crease and opens the face to guide it into the covers
back of a length outside off, Ponting pushes into the covers off the front foot. Six points for anyone who has Southee in their Fanatsy XI, since that's a maiden.
full delivery, Ponting takes it on the full and drives down the ground for one
stifled appeal as Clarke misses the flick to a ball coming into the pads sharply. Was going down the leg side though.
Clarke gets a single this time, full on the pads and driven cleanly down to long on
back of a length outside off, Ponting reaches across and drives into the covers for one
on the pads this time, worked into midwicket
over-pitched outside off, Ponting leans into a cover drive, but finds the fielder
Southee does his bit for an early finish, pushes an inducker well down the leg side. Baz, standing up, had no chance.
length ball on off stump, coming in with the angle and punched solidly into the covers
gets one to move away from Clarke, short ball wide outside off and it is hacked away to the deep
short length again, comes into the pads and whipped square for a single
back of a length on the leg stump line, Ponting hops across and looks to flick, but can't get it away

Ponting must be miffed. Hide the TV in the dressing room. Lovely work from Baz, he's stolen a wicket out of nowhere. Southee pushes another one half a foot down the leg side, Ponting is lulled out of the crease as he plays a walking flick and misses. McCullum doesn't. With hands quicker than a rattlesnake he collects and removes the bails. By the time Ponting turned back, McCullum was celebrating. Hide the TVs I say.
White beaten outside off first up, fishing at a ball angling across at decent pace and missing. Good delivery from Southee
finishes with a fuller delivery on the pads, White flicks with control, but finds midwicket
Clarke gets a gift on the pads, and just redirects it to deep square leg. Easy runs don't come any easier - full and friendly pace. No fielders in the deep to cut it off.
back of a length outside off, Clarke comes forward and defends to the off side
this time Ryder rolls one off the back of the hand and Clarke defends to the off side
this one slips down the leg side and is a couple of wides. Clarke doesn't get his backfoot out, unlike Ponting.

White is away with four as Ryder delivers a decentish back of the hand legcutter on middle and off. Nothing wrong with that ball, but not much was right either. White just got the front foot across and drove through the line for four
slower ball to end the over, wide of off stump and back of a length. White can't connect with the airy drive
another one tails in out of Southee's hand but is punched authoritatively into the covers
another legcutter from Southee, Clarke opens the face and steers it square.
fuller length on off stump, Clarke gets forward and defends into the off side
on Clarke's pads from round the stumps, worked off the pads towards midwicket
back of a length and angling across, Clarke goes for the big booming drive and gets an inside edge that squeezes past the stumps to the leg side
Southee's bowling maidens like nobody's business. Clarke cracks a short ball wide outside off straight to point
back of a length on off stump, White covers the line and defends dourly to the off side
fuller and straighter, White gets the front pad across and plays around it to defend down the track
hmm, White's getting a little restless, looks for a booming hit down the ground to a very full ball, and can't get under it
full toss on middle and off, White looks to drive into the off side, but still can't get the gap
this time White gets a single, squeezing a ball curving in, through the leg side for a couple
finishes with more defence down the ground as Ryder keeps it short of driving length
Southee gets the outside edge with another naggingly innocuous legcutter that nips off the straight. Clarke closes the face and it runs away through third man
fuller and a touch wider of off stump, White pokes it out to cover
another full ball outside off, White pushes into the covers with a half across movement.
on middle and leg, White gets the front foot across and plays into the leg side
sharp inward movement from just outside off, White stays back and opens the face to dab it down to third man
another sharpish inducker to end the over, Clarke is forward and covers the line before defending with the full face towards mid on
White plays him carefully into the cover for a single
angling across Clarke from over the wicket, he opens the face and steers it backward of point for one
width on offer outside off, and it is cracked away through point for a couple
White gets another easy single in front of square. Australia taking their time in putting a ribbon over this.
wide outside off, Clarke opens the face and defends towards point
Clarke ends the over with a couple. No pace from Franklin, no movement either, worked away easily
imperious from Clarke, short ball from Bennett - he keeps bowling these, and Clarke keeps waiting for them and pulling away. Fully in control and played in front of square for four
couple of wides down the leg side, Baz does excruciatingly well to delay the denouement. That was headed for five wides
short and wide outside off now, Bennett's run out of steam big time here. White was so early on the cut, it went through extra cover. Go figure.
and he nearly falls for a slow back-of-the-hand legcutter. Comes on a day after White leant out and played the on drive and he almost chipped straight to short midwicket.

well short of a length outside off, Bennett seems to have injured his left leg - is that knee, ankle or calf? White hangs back and plays into the off side. Looks like a calf strain. Bennett was unplayable against Kenya. Slightly different today.
bowls from well wide of the crease as he changes his action following the injury, pushed into the off side against the pace.
and four more, Clarke gets a pull shot away, running the men at deep square leg and deep midwicket. Both of them converged and fell in hope but the ball sped past. Five to win.
back of a length outside off, defends into the offside as White struggles to force it away
fuller outside off, While pushes forward defensively
a foot and a half wide outside off, White goes for the full-blooded scythe cut .. and finds point
back of a length outside off, White reaches out, opens the face and dabs it straight to short third man
scores are level. Can New Zealand force a tie? I think not. Back of a length and angling across White who part-edges, part-steers it to third man

Australia get the Chappell-Hadlee Trophy even before New Zealand could get the second new ball. Length ball, wafting past him outside off, White reaches out and steers with control through backward point to get the winning runs.
